JKOzS YwOzI pf-15_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-17_">How to apply heat transfer vinyl with iron</span></h2><p class="sc-jeqYYF hzMUYW pf-18_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-20_">Do you want to start using HTV but you don’t have a heat press? Don’t worry, you can use a household iron to apply your heat transfer vinyl.</span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-9a4954fa--179EB1E268E447b4A10235B9D5942A0B_500x.png?v=1618215889" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-9a4954fa--179EB1E268E447b4A10235B9D5942A0B.png?v=1618215889 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-9a4954fa--179EB1E268E447b4A10235B9D5942A0B_500x.png?v=1618215889 320w" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) and (max-width: 1535px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) and (max-width: 1023px) 768px, 320px" width="810" height="431" loading="lazy" alt="How to apply heat transfer vinyl with iron" title="How to apply heat transfer vinyl with iron" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-kLwgWK cVVPgF pf-21_"/><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-gSQGeZ iOAir pf-22_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-lbhJmS gRgzMw pf-23_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-25_">To begin, you need to take a clear and transparent carrier sheet (Teflon works best)so that you can read the design even after putting it on top of the material. It will protect your clothing from the exposure of intense heating and keep the clothing damage free.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-lbhJmS gRgzMw pf-26_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-28_">One of the main reasons that HTV doesn’t always adhere well when you use a household iron is that there was not enough pressure. You’ll want to really put your weight on the iron. Much more pressure is required to press vinyl than to iron clothes. Keep in mind, when you are using a heat press, there are several pounds of pressure used.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-lbhJmS gRgzMw pf-29_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-31_">Keep in mind that many irons will not maintain a consistent temperature over the entire surface. Most household irons will get the hottest right in the center. For this reason, you’ll want to make that is the area of the iron that you are using to apply your vinyl.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-lbhJmS gRgzMw pf-32_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-34_">If you realize some parts of your transfer aren’t sticking when you are peeling your carrier sheet, just put the carrier sheet back down, and press again.</span></li></ul><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-iJKOzS YwOzI pf-35_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-37_">How to apply heat transfer vinyl with heat press</span></h2><p class="sc-jeqYYF hzMUYW pf-38_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-40_">Using a heat press is easier and faster,To help you make perfect craft projects every time, here are some tips.<br></span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-54fa8b32--FD1F5DED385B448bA3016ACDCEA8CBE9_500x.png?v=1618216078" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-54fa8b32--FD1F5DED385B448bA3016ACDCEA8CBE9.png?v=1618216078 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0356/5997/2741/t/26/assets/pf-54fa8b32--FD1F5DED385B448bA3016ACDCEA8CBE9_500x.png?v=1618216078 320w" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) and (max-width: 1535px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) and (max-width: 1023px) 768px, 320px" width="810" height="431" loading="lazy" alt="How to apply heat transfer vinyl with heat press" title="How to apply heat transfer vinyl with heat press" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-kLwgWK cVVPgF pf-41_"/><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-gSQGeZ iOAir pf-42_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-lbhJmS gRgzMw pf-43_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ZOsLE HTdit pf-45_">Press power button to start heating up the machine.
